# Dynamic Forms

Use the shared schema-driven form system. Do not build one-off RHF forms when `DynamicForm` fits.

## Layout

| Concern | Path |
|---------|------|
| Types | `src/components/shared/forms/types` |
| Field inputs | `src/components/shared/forms/inputs` |
| Registry / validation | `src/components/shared/forms/lib` |
| `DynamicForm` | `src/components/shared/forms/templates` |
| Feature forms | `src/features/<feature>/components/forms` |
| Feature model types | `src/features/<feature>/types` |

## Adding a feature form

1. Define the model type under `features/<feature>/types`.
2. Put shared zod in `src/lib/schemas/<model>.ts`; reuse in FieldDefs and server actions.
3. Export a `FieldDef<T>[]` schema under `components/forms/*-form-fields.ts`.
4. Wrap `DynamicForm` in a thin named `*Form` client component.
5. Pass `isEdit`, `initialValues`, `onSubmit`, `layout`, `submitLabel` from the wrapper.
6. Wire submit with `useError().run()` + `applyServerErrors` — see `.docs/components/error-handling.md`.

```tsx
// ✅ feature wrapper
<DynamicForm<User>
  fields={userFormFields}
  layout={{ mode: LayoutMode.Single, columns: 2 }}
  isEdit={isEdit}
  initialValues={initialValues}
  onSubmit={onSubmit} // (values, form) => …
/>
```

```tsx
// ✅ submit via error pipeline
const data = await run(updateUser(values), {
  onFieldErrors: (fe) => applyServerErrors(form, fe),
})
if (data) toast.success("Saved")
```

## FieldDef rules

- Every field needs `name`, `type`, `label`, and `validation` (zod).
- `select` / `multiselect` / `radio` require static `options` arrays on the FieldDef. Load dynamic options in the `*Form` wrapper via `run(listX())`, then pass them into `build*FormFields({ …options })`. Do not fetch inside FieldDef definitions or field inputs.
- `visibleWhen` / `requiredWhen` receive full form values; hidden fields are dropped from validation.
- `hide: true` — never render (e.g. timestamps). `canEdit: false` — disabled only when `isEdit`.
- Prefer `type` from the registry; use `render` only as an escape hatch.
- New input type = one file in `inputs/` + one line in `fieldRegistry`. Nothing else.

## Constraints

- Named exports only; no `any`.
- Use shadcn `Form*` primitives inside field inputs.
- Do not add form libraries beyond RHF + zod.
- Layout modes: `LayoutMode.Single` | `MultiStep` | `Tabs` (match `section` keys to step/tab keys).

See `.docs/components/forms.md` for the full human guide.
